ğŸ”¥ Core Principles

Stability first â€” Product One is a live demo for pitch, testing, and early UX validation.
All contributions should preserve stability and avoid introducing regressions.

Washington Event Spine is sacred â€”
Event shapes, naming conventions, and IDs must match /src/events/* and cannot be altered without explicit approval.

Mock-only environment â€”
No backend calls, no persistence, no FastAPI.
VIA is a mocked simulation only.

Pixel-perfect UX consistency â€”
UI changes must align with the Washington design direction and existing components.

Small PR philosophy â€”
Every change should be scoped, reviewed, tested, and isolated.

